  <h3>Taking Action</h3>
  <hr/>
  <p>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Taking action can be as simple as donating a calculator to a child in need. With your help, we can donate as many calculators as possible! Each calculation that GoodCalc makes, goes towards the education of underprivileged students around the world beginning with Africa. GoodCalc has partnered with a non-profit organization called <a href = "http://www.developafrica.org/mission-and-vision">Develop Africa Inc.</a> in order get those calculators in the hands of the African students. Furthermore, GoodCalc is still looking for potential partners and organizations that could help distribute donated calculators to other developing nations. If you are or know of a potential partner, don't be shy and contact us! Please look at the contact information at the bottom of the page.
  </p>
  </br>

  <h3>Why GoodCalc?</h3>
  <hr/>
  <p>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;People have been asking me why I just don't donate a calculator myself and call it a day. Why create an online calculator and share it with everyone? Anyone can just Google calculations or just use a physical calculator at hand such a Ti-83 plus any Texas Instrument or HP Calculator. I understand the points that they are making, however, they misunderstand why I made GoodCalc. So I want to share the reaons why I made GoodCalc to everyone. </br></br>
    1. The reason why I just don't donate a calculator myself is because I want as many people as possible to get involved. GoodCalc is a good way to spread to word about the problem at hand. In a way, with GoodCalc, everyone can help out even a little bit, and that little bit can make a difference. This way, everyone together can donate a greater number of calculators compared to the amount I can donate as an individual.</br></br>
    2. I am not trying to convert people from their everyday methods of doing calculations to using GoodCalc as their primary calculator. I am just asking people to use the calculator whenever they want to help out and support the cause. That's it! Also, to share the calculator with friends and family to spread the word!
  </p>
